Mavoko MP Patrick Makau has called for the reshuffle of police officers from Mlolongo Police Station over increased insecurity.Makau said there could be rogue officers who collude with criminals to terrorize traders and residents of Mlolongo, Syokimau and their environs.&ldquo;We have serious security problems in Mavoko especially Mlolongo, three people lost their lives after they were shot by armed bandits in Mlolongo town last week,&rdquo; said Makau.He addressed the press in Syokimau on Friday.Makau said the officers should be interrogated and legal action taken against those found capable of colluding with criminals in the region.